result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) and Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs) was dismissed by the court.

  • Kaleb W. Wusterbarth was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:38 a.m. Defendant Kaleb W. Wusterbarth in court with attorney John E Voorhees.  Defendant Kaleb W. Wusterbarth in custody.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Calling 15cf98, 15cf204, 15tr989, 15tr2173, 15tr2174 and 15tr2175. Plea questionaire filed in 15cf98. Voorhees statement to defendant's eligibility for OWI treatment court. State moves to dismiss - 15tr989, 15tr2173, 15tr2174 and 15tr2175 - Granted.  

In 15cf98 - State moves to dismiss Counts 1, 2, 3 and 5 - Granted.  Defendant pleads guilty to Count 4.   Court reads on waiver of rights and tendering plea. Waiver free and voluntary. Court finds that a factual basis for the plea exists and finds defendant guilty. Court adjourns sentencing. 

In 15cf204 
State files Information amending Count 1 to OWI - 4th w/i 5 years, Count 2 - Operating w/PAC (4th) .122, Count 3 - Bail Jumping - Felony. Schiek states that complaint is being amended to reflect charges in Information. Voorhees accepts oral amendment of criminal complaint - Stipulates receipt of law enforcement reports - Court finds probable cause exists - Judicial notice taken of 15cf98. Off record for discussion of new charges.
  Defendant waives preliminary hearing. Waiver free and voluntary. Court finds that probable cause exists and binds over. Voorhees in receipt of Information - waive reading - guilty plea entered to Count 1.
State moves to dismiss Count 2 and 3 - Granted. Plea questionaire filed. 
Defendant pleads guilty to Count 1.   Court reads on waiver of rights and tendering plea. Waiver free and voluntary. Court finds that a factual basis for the plea exists and finds defendant guilty. Court adjourns sentencing. 
Bail continued.
Adj. 11:06 a.m.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for October 28, 2015 at 02:30 pm.
